---
source: crates/tirith/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: stdout.to_string()
---
Scan files for hidden content and config poisoning

Usage: tirith scan [OPTIONS] [PATH]

Arguments:
  [PATH]  Path to scan (directory or file)

Options:
      --file <FILE>        Scan a single file explicitly
      --stdin              Read content from stdin
      --ci                 Exit non-zero in CI when findings meet threshold
      --fail-on <FAIL_ON>  Severity threshold for CI failure [default: critical]
      --format <FORMAT>    Output format (default: human) [possible values: human, json, sarif]
      --ignore <IGNORE>    Patterns to ignore
      --include <INCLUDE>  Include only files matching these patterns
      --exclude <EXCLUDE>  Exclude files matching these patterns (same as --ignore)
      --profile <PROFILE>  Load a named scan profile from policy
  -h, --help               Print help

Examples:
  tirith scan ./
  tirith scan --ci --fail-on high ./
  tirith scan --format sarif ./ > results.sarif
